  "prompt": "What are some unknown facts about the Nehru-Gandhi dynasty?",
  "response": "Here are some lesser-known facts about the Nehru-Gandhi dynasty:\n\n1. Origins\n- Jawaharlal Nehru's family was originally from Kashmir and had Kashmiri Pandit roots\n- The family was initially known as \"Nehru\" before adopting the \"Gandhi\" surname through marriage\n\n2. Family Background\n- Motilal Nehru, Jawaharlal's father, was a wealthy lawyer and prominent nationalist\n- The family was financially well-off and highly educated compared to many contemporaries\n\n3. Personal Details\n- Indira Gandhi was not actually born with the Gandhi surname; she took it after marrying Feroze Gandhi\n- Rajiv Gandhi was initially an airline pilot before entering politics\n- Sonia Gandhi was an Italian citizen before becoming an Indian political figure\n\n4. Political Journey\n- Jawaharlal Nehru was the first Prime Minister of independent India\n- Indira Gandhi was the first and, to date, only female Prime Minister of India\n- Rajiv Gandhi became Prime Minister after his mother's assassination\n\n5. Lesser-Known Connections\n- The family has complex international connections and educational backgrounds\n- They maintained significant diplomatic and intellectual networks globally\n\nThese facts provide a nuanced perspective on the dynasty's history and background.",
